					<description><![CDATA[<p>With a failing heart and little hope of healing, Alan Lewis sunk into depression, gaining 330 pounds. After he came to Mayo, bariatric surgery enabled the transplant he'd sought for so many years. &amp;#160;&amp;#160; Alan Lewis was lying on the floor — the only position that eased his discomfort — watching a football game. When [&amp;#8230;]</p>
