					<description><![CDATA[<p>ROCHESTER, Minn. — Mayo Clinic Transplant achieved the highest annual transplant volume in its history in 2025 by performing 2,065 solid organ transplants across its Arizona, Florida and Minnesota campuses, according to data from the Organ Procurement and Transplantation Network (OPTN). The new record surpasses 2,006 transplanted solid organs in 2024 and 1,952 in 2023, [&amp;#8230;]</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://newsnetwork.mayoclinic.org/discussion/mayo-clinic-transplant-performs-record-2065-organ-transplants-in-2025/">Mayo Clinic Transplant performs record 2,065 organ transplants in 2025</a> appeared first on <a href="https://newsnetwork.mayoclinic.org">Mayo Clinic News Network</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[
<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="577" src="https://newsnetwork.mayoclinic.org/n7-mcnn/7bcc9724adf7b803/uploads/2026/01/MCA-Craig-Scherer_First-lung-transplant-recipient_16x9-1024x577.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-409561" srcset="https://newsnetwork.mayoclinic.org/n7-mcnn/7bcc9724adf7b803/uploads/2026/01/MCA-Craig-Scherer_First-lung-transplant-recipient_16x9-1024x577.jpg 1024w, https://newsnetwork.mayoclinic.org/n7-mcnn/7bcc9724adf7b803/uploads/2026/01/MCA-Craig-Scherer_First-lung-transplant-recipient_16x9-300x169.jpg 300w, https://newsnetwork.mayoclinic.org/n7-mcnn/7bcc9724adf7b803/uploads/2026/01/MCA-Craig-Scherer_First-lung-transplant-recipient_16x9-768x433.jpg 768w, https://newsnetwork.mayoclinic.org/n7-mcnn/7bcc9724adf7b803/uploads/2026/01/MCA-Craig-Scherer_First-lung-transplant-recipient_16x9.jpg 1536w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></figure>



<p>ROCHESTER, Minn. — <a href="https://www.mayoclinic.org/departments-centers/transplant-center/home/orc-20203891" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Mayo Clinic Transplant</a> achieved the highest annual transplant volume in its history in 2025 by performing 2,065 solid organ transplants across its Arizona, Florida and Minnesota campuses, according to data from the <a href="https://www.hrsa.gov/optn" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Organ Procurement and Transplantation Network (OPTN)</a>.</p>



<p>The new record surpasses 2,006 transplanted solid organs in 2024 and 1,952 in 2023, reflecting Mayo Clinic's dedication to saving more lives through continued advances in transplantation driven by new research, technology and innovation.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="576" src="https://newsnetwork.mayoclinic.org/n7-mcnn/7bcc9724adf7b803/uploads/2026/01/Transplant-Center-Infographic-FINAL_1920x1080_News-Network-1024x576.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-409723" srcset="https://newsnetwork.mayoclinic.org/n7-mcnn/7bcc9724adf7b803/uploads/2026/01/Transplant-Center-Infographic-FINAL_1920x1080_News-Network-1024x576.jpg 1024w, https://newsnetwork.mayoclinic.org/n7-mcnn/7bcc9724adf7b803/uploads/2026/01/Transplant-Center-Infographic-FINAL_1920x1080_News-Network-300x169.jpg 300w, https://newsnetwork.mayoclinic.org/n7-mcnn/7bcc9724adf7b803/uploads/2026/01/Transplant-Center-Infographic-FINAL_1920x1080_News-Network-768x432.jpg 768w, https://newsnetwork.mayoclinic.org/n7-mcnn/7bcc9724adf7b803/uploads/2026/01/Transplant-Center-Infographic-FINAL_1920x1080_News-Network-1536x864.jpg 1536w, https://newsnetwork.mayoclinic.org/n7-mcnn/7bcc9724adf7b803/uploads/2026/01/Transplant-Center-Infographic-FINAL_1920x1080_News-Network-2048x1152.jpg 2048w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></figure>



<p>"This number represents new beginnings full of hope for so many," says <a href="https://www.mayoclinic.org/biographies/heimbach-julie-k-m-d/bio-20054676" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Julie Heimbach, M.D.</a>, transplant surgeon and director of <a href="https://www.mayoclinic.org/departments-centers/transplant-center/home/orc-20203891" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Mayo Clinic Transplant in Rochester</a>. "This incredible milestone is only made possible by the generosity of our donors and donor families, the resilience of our transplant recipients, and the unwavering dedication of our transplant care teams."</p>



<p>The record volume is encouraging, as the number of patients waiting on the national transplant list remains daunting. <a href="https://unos.org/data/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">More than 109,000 people in the U.S.</a> are currently waiting for lifesaving organs, according to OPTN data. &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="769" src="https://newsnetwork.mayoclinic.org/n7-mcnn/7bcc9724adf7b803/uploads/2026/01/MCF-A.J.-Smith_Kidney-Transplant-Recipient-1024x769.jpeg" alt="" class="wp-image-409562" srcset="https://newsnetwork.mayoclinic.org/n7-mcnn/7bcc9724adf7b803/uploads/2026/01/MCF-A.J.-Smith_Kidney-Transplant-Recipient-1024x769.jpeg 1024w, https://newsnetwork.mayoclinic.org/n7-mcnn/7bcc9724adf7b803/uploads/2026/01/MCF-A.J.-Smith_Kidney-Transplant-Recipient-300x225.jpeg 300w, https://newsnetwork.mayoclinic.org/n7-mcnn/7bcc9724adf7b803/uploads/2026/01/MCF-A.J.-Smith_Kidney-Transplant-Recipient-768x576.jpeg 768w, https://newsnetwork.mayoclinic.org/n7-mcnn/7bcc9724adf7b803/uploads/2026/01/MCF-A.J.-Smith_Kidney-Transplant-Recipient-1536x1153.jpeg 1536w, https://newsnetwork.mayoclinic.org/n7-mcnn/7bcc9724adf7b803/uploads/2026/01/MCF-A.J.-Smith_Kidney-Transplant-Recipient.jpeg 2048w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></figure>



<p>To meet this need, Mayo Clinic teams are advancing the science and delivery of transplantation through initiatives such as:</p>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><a href="https://newsnetwork.mayoclinic.org/discussion/video-eliminating-the-need-for-lifelong-immunosuppressive-medications-for-transplant-patients/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Exploring the use of stem cells to prevent organ rejection.</a></li>



<li><a href="https://newsnetwork.mayoclinic.org/discussion/heart-transplant-innovation-new-heart-in-a-box-technology-provides-gift-of-life-to-arizona-man-as-couple-prepares-to-celebrate-50-year-anniversary/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Using normothermic machine perfusion to improve organ preservation.</a></li>



<li><a href="https://www.mayoclinic.org/departments-centers/paired-donation/overview/ovc-20508454" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Expanding living donor paired exchange programs.</a></li>



<li><a href="https://www.mayoclinic.org/medical-professionals/transplant-medicine/news/five-ways-artificial-intelligence-promises-to-transform-organ-transplant/mac-20548221" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Researching artificial intelligence to transform organ transplant.</a></li>
</ul>



<p>"Our work doesn't stop with the patients we serve today," says Dr. Heimbach. "Through collaboration across Mayo Clinic teams, investing in new technologies, and continued research, we are working toward a future where we can expand access and help more patients receive lifesaving transplants when they need them most."</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-full"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" width="1024" height="576" src="https://newsnetwork.mayoclinic.org/n7-mcnn/7bcc9724adf7b803/uploads/2026/01/MCR-Brady-Larson-graduation.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-409563" srcset="https://newsnetwork.mayoclinic.org/n7-mcnn/7bcc9724adf7b803/uploads/2026/01/MCR-Brady-Larson-graduation.jpg 1024w, https://newsnetwork.mayoclinic.org/n7-mcnn/7bcc9724adf7b803/uploads/2026/01/MCR-Brady-Larson-graduation-300x169.jpg 300w, https://newsnetwork.mayoclinic.org/n7-mcnn/7bcc9724adf7b803/uploads/2026/01/MCR-Brady-Larson-graduation-768x432.jpg 768w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></figure>



<p>As 2026 begins, transplant teams move forward with gratitude for the lives saved and a continued commitment to those who are still waiting.</p>



<p>###</p>



<p><strong>About Mayo Clinic</strong><br><a href="https://www.mayoclinic.org/about-mayo-clinic" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Mayo Clinic</a>&amp;nbsp;is a nonprofit organization committed to innovation in clinical practice, education and research, and providing compassion, expertise and answers to everyone who needs healing. Visit the&amp;nbsp;<a href="https://newsnetwork.mayoclinic.org/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Mayo Clinic News Network</a>&amp;nbsp;for additional Mayo Clinic news.</p>



<p><strong>About Mayo Clinic Transplant</strong> <br><a href="https://www.mayoclinic.org/departments-centers/transplant-center/home/orc-20203891" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Mayo Clinic Transplant</a> is one of the largest and most comprehensive transplant programs in the world. With programs in Arizona, Florida and Minnesota, Mayo Clinic provides seamless, coordinated care across heart, lung, liver, kidney, pancreas and bone marrow transplantation for both adults and children. Guided by a commitment to innovation, research and education, Mayo Clinic Transplant delivers world-leading outcomes, compassionate patient care and advances that shape the future of transplantation worldwide. Mayo Clinic Transplant delivers world-leading outcomes, compassionate patient care and advances that shape the future of transplantation worldwide.</p>



